content.description: This is slightly contrived, but very good! Climb the north Arete, starts vert with good holds, but about 20 ft up the angle eases off and the holds disappear. slap up the arete and smear your feet, and a few moves lead to solid feet and decent crimps. can also drift right around the blank spot, keeps it 5.9. Second cruxy section is the upper headwall, left if 5.10-, the right is 5.11+
content.protection: Use the second set of anchors from the north, keeps you from swinging around the corner. Super long slings help.

content.description: Second set of bolts from the left (north). The route climbs 5.8 slab up to a headwall. The left side of the headwall is 5.9 and the center appears to be 5.11
content.location: Second set of bolts from the left (north)

content.description: Far right route (south). Fun slab with a steeper section towards the end. Many variations to add or decrease difficulty.
content.protection:
TR

Two new bolts, and two old bolts. Drop the rope left for the 5.8 finish, or near the newer wedge bolt for the kid friendly 5.5 finish.

content.description: Second route from the right (south). Crux at the end. You can set the TR to skip the crux and go up an easy ramp to the right. Many variations to add or decrease difficulty.
